I have been with this Medical Office for over a year now. I no longer dread seeing my Doctor. Every Employee that I have had contact with has been a pleasure. Very kind & professional. After check in while waiting for my Doctor I listen to the Staff outside & I marvel at how happy & cheerful they sound. It says alot to hear the happy Staff because that tells me they have a great Supervisor that they work for. I also hear other People who are waiting for the Doctor complain about the wait time. I know being in pain is unpleasant but my Doctor takes the complaining in stride and is cheerful and upbeat always. I am treated with respect & compassion. The goal is always to get me healed and moving forward in my Health. The plan is discussed, agreed to and very encouraging. From the time of arrival the first impression is welcoming & warm. Check in & taken to the back I am always asked "How are you today?" And that's not just a standard greeting. They really want to know! And upon conclusion, making my next appointment I am asked what works best for MY schedule?  Yes I reccomend this Company. Be prepared to wait a little time. <UserId.>108711408262571584093<//UserId.>< Name>
Jim Thornburg</Name>
<time>1435612141424</time><Rate>4<//Rate>< Text>
My wife and I were searching for lunch one day and decided to try the new Japanese place, Sansai, on a whim. The interior is clean, not too busy, with attractive tables and booths. An open kitchen so you can see that the cooks are being honest with a cold bar behind glass holding the salad options. I must say I was a little confused by the ordering process, but really it's straight forward. I'm just a little dumb.
We ordered a chicken plate and some kind of a sushi roll (I can't remember now to save my life!). Both were excellent and tasted fresh. I was a little concerned about ordering sushi rolls, and not just a plain old California Roll that you can get from a gas station, but with actual sushi fish on it. Luckily it tasted fine and was not tainted or old. I really liked the salad that came with the entree, and the tomato and cucumber salad on the side. Chicken was not fatty or dry. It was great! We spent about $17 for 2 of us to share a lunch, so it's definitely on the pricey side, especially for a place that comes off as a quick-serve restaurant. But the good news is that the food is good so hopefully this place does well and keeps Restaurant Row looking great!< /Text>

< Text>
Want value?  Yes, SanSai!

Want delicious food?  Yes, SanSai!

Want a quick meal?  Yes, SanSai!

Will we, Cobra Kai, beat the Miyagi Dojo at the All-Valley Karate Tournament?  Yes, SanSai!

SanSai is a quick casual Japanese food spot, located in Lakewood's Restaurant Row (aka Candlewood St.) across the mall.  Specials galore, including daily, lunch & Happy Hour.

Spicy miso ramen-
With a cool overcast day & myself feeling a little chilly, I knew a nice bowl of piping hot ramen would be in store for me.  SanSai has tonkatsu & spicy miso as their ramen options.  Spicy miso is my go-to everywhere, so spicy miso it was.  In a large bowl, the steaming soup of happiness was plentiful.  While the ramen could've been a little more al dente for my personal taste, the chewiness was there and the tender slices of pork were succulent and delicious.  The half egg was a bonus, as I know some popular ramen shops charge extra for that.  Upon receiving my order, I asked for chili oil, as I didn't want to use Sriracha because of the preservatives.  A sauce cup of chili oil was quickly brought to me, upon which I dumped the entire contents into my spicy miso, delivering the right amount of heat I desired.  I happily slurped & gulped it down to the very last drop.  For $8+, the spicy miso ramen was good & about on par with dedicated ramen restaurants.

Plentiful seating, with booths, stools & a communal table.  Service was good.  The menu states ramen takes about 10-15 mins, of which I only waited approximately 5 mins or so for mine.  I was the first customer of the day, however.

Parking is in a private lot, shared by Outback Steakhouse and other businesses.

During my meal of ramen & California roll, I enjoyed listening to Sirius satellite radio on the house speakers.  When I was finishing my soup, it happened.  Yes, it happened!  I was Rick Roll'd!

"Never gonna give you up, never gonna let you down.
Never gonna run around, and desert you."

Aye aye, SanSai!  SanSai offers up delicious Japanese food in a casual setting.  I haven't had ramen in a long while, since the LALALA Ramen Pass promo, so SanSai's spicy miso hit the spot.  Add to that the daily, lunch & Happy Hour specials, and SanSai has a new fan.  Quick, convenient & yummy, I highly recommend SanSai!

NOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOM</Text>

<Gmap_id>0x808e3545c8e9ec93:0x114c9a4a2819060e< /Gmap_id>< review>
Dave from Attic Star is a very hard worker, personable and really puts forth a strong effort to help resolve rodent issues which can be very complex.

That said it's important to understand that the owner Sean decided 8 months ago that the company will not take jobs on homes that have skip sheathed roofs as work can not be guaranteed.

Many older homes dating from the 80's and older especially if they have tile roofs that have not been re-roofed will not be something they can help with due to the high level of complexity in alleviating entry points.

This means that unless you have full sheathing on your roof (full plywood pieces under your roofing) that this is not the right company for you.

Also they have a minimum fee of $2000.00 (Two Thousand dollers) so if you think your issue may be a smaller one or you don't have a larger budget perhaps just have them out for a consult to learn more then hire a handy person to help seal problem areas.

These guys are quite intelligent, real chess players so for the most part I'm sure you would be in good hands if you qualify as a customer.

Do your homework, educate yourself ahead of time so you can understand a bit about your issue and methods for resolving it.

They turned me down as a possible client all together due to my skip sheathed roof which is mostly understandable.

The reason I say mostly is beacause despite the fact that the attic can potentially be used for them (rodents) to access the crawl space (under the home) using the bathroom, laundry room and kitchen plumbing vents if they were not properly sealed at time of construction. To go up and down within a home inside the walls.

It is possible to seal these vent areas to isolate the attic from the crawl space. Firecode calls for these gaps to be sealed in modern homes from the 80's and later. So the crawl space should be able to be sealed off seperately from the attic to help mitigate issues regardless of a skip sheathed roof.

These being the facts I was still turned down as a potential client to help with the crawl space as I requested until I can finish sheathing my roof in its entirety.

This is their right of course just disappointing for me as an owner who is trying to alleviate a problem.</review>

< Review>
Chuck/Alex, thank you.  Roughly 18-months ago we decided it was time to replace our old blown-in insulation with nice thick R-38 "Batts."  Immediately we noticed our energy consumption reduced, making this a clear upgrade for any future home we own.

With that said, Chuck really went above and beyond my expectations for customer service.  After initial installation, Chuck followed up and made sure I was satisfied with the results.  I asked how long it normally took for the Batts to fluff up properly...rather than giving some answer like "wait a little longer," Chuck recommended his guys review during the follow up visit.  There were a few locations where the insulation snagged while fluffing and his guys took care of it.

Second instance was when we noticed a critter running around the attic.  We called Chuck about a year after initial install and he sent over his guys to check mesh around crawl space and roof vents.  A few vents had been damaged, so his guys put new screens on...no charge! ("killer" warranty with Attic Star)

Third time we noticed a second critter rummaging around...Called Chuck, and found out our bathroom contractor used a roof vent without mesh!!! What the heck! Perfectly contained with Attic Star then our contractor messes things up.  Chuck brought his guys out and found the entry point almost instantly! These guys have really stood by their warranty, even when it wasn't their fault.  A+++ customer service.  Will use again!</Review>

<Rating>5< /Rating>< Review>
We recently bought a bank owned home that was vacant for several years.  During this time about 20 pigeons took residence in the attic where they proceeded to give birth in many nests scattered across the attic, and lets just say they used the bathroom in very square inch of our 5,000 sq ft. attic.

We called another attic service and they came out and took an hour and a half to look around. They said they have never seen a job as big as this one.  During this hour and a half they kept asking a ton of questions and going over the same information which was very interrupting to my day with my toddler. After all of that they and gave us a $15,000 estimate!  What!! We said thanks but no thanks to those guys.

We called Ron and his team with Attic Star and he came out in a day to take a look, and was early for the appointment.  Ron spent about 15 mins in the attic (did I mention the other guys were here for 1 1/2 hours?) and lets just say his estimate was wayyy under 15k for the same job.  Since we booked right then he gave us an additional discount.  Ron also said he had done jobs with rodents and birds much larger than this, which gave me a lot of confidence.  Before he left I asked if he wanted my phone number in case he was running late and he said there was no need because he would be here right on time.
And he was right on time, actually early.  Before they started they put down floor covering and made sure everything was all set up before I left for work.  My husband went home for lunch to take a look at the progress.  Ron likes for you to check their work periodically. We returned about 4 hours later and they were just finishing up spraying the new installation into the attic.  I actually went up into the attic for the first time to take a look. They packed up everything and there was not a trace that they have ever been here expect for the clean attic.  At one point we considered doing the job ourselves, but with the great cost Attic Star can give you, you won't be saving very much doing it yourself. I would highly recommend Attic Star to anyone who has a crappy job that needs a good cleaning "no pun intended!"< /Review>

<review>We called on Attic Star to do a full clean-out out of our attic, including removal of old insulation, patching up holes that rodents, etc. had been using, and disinfecting the surfaces from rodent droppings as well as a clean out of our crawlspace and HVAC system.

Ron and his crew were efficient and thorough throughout the process. During the bid process he explained everything in detail and showed pictures of the current state of our attic (which needed a lot of attention). He explained the entire process step by step and, during the job, he made good on his word to show me the various stages along the way and the work that had been done. They made sure to protect our floors, doors, walls, etc from any potential damage/dirt and cleaned up after they were done.

The only drawback to the entire process was the unnecessary pressure to sign the bid and write a review both on the spot and after the service. These were unnecessary tactics for a company that prides itself on its reputation. Allow the customer some space.

Having said that, Ron and his team did a great job and have guaranteed their work.<//review>< pictures>

<rating>5<//rating>< text>
My 2007 Honda Accord needed some base enhancement so I stop by PCH Custom Audio to see what they have in terms of a amplified subwoofer. They didn't have any but Sam and Oscar, was knowledgeable and very helpful in picking the right amplifier and woofer and an enclosure. I got a Kicker 40KX200.2 amp, a Kicker 43C104 Comp 10" and an enclosure for $200 bucks out the door. He put the speaker in the enclosure for me. I took it home, installed it and it sounds very deep. More than I expected. I am a repeat customer and they always give me a good deal. Just hit Sam up for all your car enhancement needs.< /text>

Lived here from May 2018-May 2019.
It‚Äôs a pretty nice place and close to freeway and stores. The master bedroom closet and bathrooms are large for an apartment. The ceiling is higher than average. Whenever something breaks, the maintenance is amazing and fixes it very quickly. However that being said. If coming home after 7, forget about any parking near your apartment. You will have to park across the complex in the spots next to fences because there will be none otherwise. I literally would not go anywhere after 6 because I have a baby and I didn‚Äôt want to carry a car seat that far. The amenities(theater and game room, pool table)are nice but only open from 9-6 Monday through Saturday and if you work a normal 9-5 you will pretty much never use them. On Saturdays, there are way too many people at the pool so rarely used it. One pool for such a massive complex is ridiculous. The gym, jacuzzi, and fireplace area are open longer (I believe til 10?)so I got to enjoy those amenities more often. The tanning bed did NOT work once in the entire time I was there. Gate is broken half the time. I asked about security before moving in and was told yes they have some but never saw them. Smoking is allowed here outside. The management was ridiculous. I received at least 3 false evictions notices each one around 8pm so I couldn‚Äôt talk to office until the next morning. I wouldn‚Äôt be able to sleep and would have to call in late to work the next morning to figure them out each time because I was keeping up with rent/bills with no other potential issues that would possibly evict me. Apparently the office doesn‚Äôt know how to math because they would keep saying we owed them money but every time I talked to a manager and told them to figure it out they said sorry our mistake.(we even ended up having a credit on the last month). We actually bought a house in January and tried to move out but they said in order to move out earlier we would have to pay for an additional 3 months rent. Our rent was 1,880 for a 2bed 2 bath. Thats $5,640 without their ‚Äúmove out‚Äù fees. Literally crazy. Barely 6 weeks after we turned in our keys we received a bill stating they have been trying to mail us and because we haven‚Äôt paid our move out fees our account had the possibility of going to collections. This was our first notice so of course we sent a check right away. Attached is a picture of their move out fees. I called and asked about the weird charges. Floor level is a charge for living on the first floor. Global fees are the amenities (even though they were already included in our last months rent). My apartment was cleaned professionally but because I couldn‚Äôt get a detailed invoice (copy of check doesn‚Äôt count) I ended up paying the apartments again for their ‚Äúcleaning‚Äù. Honestly a nice area but the garbage I had to deal with was unacceptable. If your desperate for a nice place to live, come here. If you want peace of mind, go somewhere else.</Review>

<user_id>110689151096892148409<//user_id>< text>
This is the nicest apartment I have ever lived in--and I've moved and been many places in my lifetime.  Conveniently located near the Roseville Galleria mall, lots of shopping nearby, easy access to Hwy 65.  Downstairs apartment has wood floors, except for carpet in each bedroom, granite counter tops, high ceilings, gas fireplace (not for wood).  Nice pool area with lounge chairs for people's use.  Gas grills near the pool need to be reserved in advance. Repair requests are acknowledged quickly and repairs done in a very reasonable period of time--very nice.
Decent mix of people live here, both racially and age-wise.  Like most apartment living, everyone seems to just go about their own business.  Most apartments come with their own garage; some are cheaper and have an outside "Reserved" spot instead.
Management has a somewhat draconian policy towards late payments--no warning phone call, nothing.  I had changed my method of payment on their website, but accidentally had somehow not taken the extra step to activate it (not obvious btw).  A day or two after the payment was late resulted in a 3-day Notice to Quit on my door.  Not friendly. No phone call, no text.  Had to take off of work to get a cashiers check to rectify the situation.
Over-all I like it here and will likely live here a minimum of two years.< /text>

<rating>1< /rating>< text>
The issues with JRK Management and The Terraces at Highland Reserve are endless! We have had ongoing issues with the upstairs neighbors, and complaints to management have gone unnoticed and unresolved. We believe, due to these issues, we have now been targeted by management and have begun to receive parking violation notices on our vehicles, while vehicles committing the same violations one spot over, have no notices.

Issue #1
On the morning of Friday January 20th we awoke to a parking violation notice on our Ford Taurus, which was parked in a visitor spot. The violation was due to a red sticker car being in a visitor spot, however, pictures I took on that same morning show a number of resident vehicles, with red stickers, being parked in visitor spots, with no notices of violation. Now, it's no secret that the parking at the Terraces is deplorable, which is why vehicles end up parking in these visitor spots overnight. Furthermore, we find this violation notice to be a blatant, targeted, attack against us, and only one in a long line of issues with this place.

Issue #2
On the morning of Sunday January 29th, we again awoke to a violation notice, this time on our Ford Focus, this one for a blue sticker car being parked outside the garage. In the 5 months we've lived here, my blue sticker car has been parked outside more than a handful of times, overnight, with zero attention. This also is being received as a targeted attack against us, as there were no other notices on any other blue or red stickered cars that morning which were parked incorrectly, and there were many other potential violations, as usual.

Issue #3
This morning, as I left for work, I noticed a number of violations, again, with no notices at all. A blue truck, which has been playing musical parking spots, bouncing from visitor spot to visitor spot for months, has yet to receive a violation, and it has no sticker of any kind. I believe there is a stipulation in the lease dictating how long a visitor can stay consecutively, so if this is in face a visitor, it would constitute a violation. If it's a tenant, also it would constitute a violation, surely more of a violation than either of my cars being parked for one night. In addition, the on-site property manager's Nissan Cube was photographed parked in a visitor spot. As we've already discussed with management about the pool being locked during regular use hours, it is vehemently unacceptable for on-site staff to be given special privileges, while the paying tenants are not. Finally, another car was seen this morning, next to mine, to have a red sticker, in a visitor spot, with no notice. All of these vehicles had enough condensation on the windows to deduce, with reasonable certainty, that they had been parked overnight, and should have received notices.

Issue #4
The upstairs neighbors continue to be an outstanding issue. Our calls to the after hours line went unresolved. The neighbors continue to wake us up before 5:30 every morning, stay up with loud banging noises on all walls and floor well past 10:00pm every night. It has also become common for us to be woken up in the middle of the night, as late as midnight and 2am in many cases, to loud noises against the wall, sounds of a dog running back and forth through the house, and loud voices and yelling. Still, these issues are unresolved, yet we had the courtesy officer dispatched to our apartment the other night with claims we had played loud music after 10pm. He informed us the call came in at 10pm on the dot. He entered my apartment, and I let him listen to the volume of our TV, which had not changed for over 2 hours, and the time of his visit was 10:30pm. So now we have provable evidence of false accusations, made by the neighbors, regarding our actions, yet we have no resolution to their issues.

I strongly advise anyone considering The Terraces at Highland Reserve, or any other JRK management property, to look elsewhere. The lack of care and service received by management is unbelievably horrible, by far the worst I've dealt with in my life.< /text>

I would NOT recommend this complex to anyone. For starters, almost everyone on the officr staff is rude. They will be very brief with you as if it is a pain for them to have to speak with you. Also, the apartment that we moved into had several problems. When we first moved in during the summer, the a.c. unit was not functioning properly. We called maintenance to request someone to fix it, and it took them several days to come to our apartment. The maintenance man told us that it was a switch that was not turned on. This is something that should have been addressed prior to move in, especially considering the fact that we moved in during the summer. Another problem we encountered at move in was a gas leak. No one on the staff caught this prior to us moving in, and that should be a red flag to whoever is reading this. A gas leak can be a very dangerous situation, and it seems that the staff must not realize this, because it took them several weeks to repair it. During that time, we had to cook and shower in an dirty apartment a couple buildings away. Once winter came around, the heater was not working. After putting in a maintenance request, we again waited many days for them to fix it. They did not show up on the day they said they would, and when they finally did the next day, it turned out to be that they had turned off the heater for the summer and failed to inform us.  On top of this was a plumbing problem with our apartment that took them another few days to get to. When we gave our 60-day notice, they tried to get us to turn in our keys 6 days early and yet still charge us the $500 in rent associated with those 6 days. My roommate discussed this with one of the women in the office, and the woman was rudely saying we had to turn in the keys early and still pay the extra money. Finally, another women from the office came out and said that the other woman was wrong, and that we could keep the keys for those 6 days. The way that the office staff treats its residents (who pay an exorbitant amount of money to live in this awful place) is appauling. I don't know how any of them have a job dealing with people. The last thing they did was to charge us extra money upon move out. My roommates and I kept the apartment in extremely good conditon throughout the entire time we lived there. On top of this, we spent an additional 15 hours cleaning the apartment one final time. We left the apartment in better condition than it was when we received it. During our time there, one of the maintenance workers even told me that our apartment was one of the cleanest he had seen in his time there. Yet they still took our entire deposit and charged us an additional amount of money for cleaning. Therefore, DO NOT MOVE INTO THESE APARTMENTS. You will get ripped off, treated with disrespect by the office staff, deal with several repairs needed in your apartment, and it will take forever to get anything fixed, even if it is high priority. I went to the Lodi dealer as I received a recall notice. And decided to get the oil changed also on my 2013 Chrysler 300. When the car was finished I noticed the easy exit seat was not working properly. I brought it to the attention of the service guy Tom. He said since I didn't have memory seat buttons on the driver's door that it was impossible for the easy exit seat to operate. I explained to Tom that the easy exit seat was working and has been since I bought the car in 2014or 15. He said he was too busy with other customers to help me and that I should call the Chrysler dealer. , I told him that I would. In the meantime I got on YouTube. And find the video that fixes the easy exit seat. And to do that you turn your car on put the seat all the way back, then put the seat all the way forward put the seat all the way back put the seat all the way forward and then put it all the way back again. Turn off your car. Then turn it back on. And the seat went right back to where it was supposed to be and the telescoping Steering wheel also return to where it should be. So, thanks to the YouTube video. I was able to fix the problem that Tom ignore me about. That's why I only the two stars. And I want to say that this is not a reflection on the rest of the staff. Summer 2018 (June)

< Text>
In 2003, I bought my new Jeep Grand Cherokee from a different dealership on this lot.  I have only 56K miles on my Jeep to date.  I do a lot of my own service because of bad and poor experiences in the past.  The experience I have had at Lodi CDJR is one just as bad if not worse.  I originally took my Jeep in on 8/6/16 to have the air bag recall performed and to get an estimate for a check engine light.  (smog related).  For my jeep when it comes to smog issue, I want factory parts. Lodi CDJR furnishes a courtesy shuttle. (I need to rely on the courtesy vehicle because my Jeep is our only vehicle)  My Jeep was ready that day for pickup  (parts were ordered and I needed the vehicle ). I asked if the shuttle could pick me up. I was asked what time. I said 1 o'clock. They agreed.  I waited until 2:30 to call the dealer asking where my ride was. I was told they were just leaving.  I brought my Jeep in first thing Monday morning and got a ride home on the shuttle. At around 11:30 I was called saying my Jeep was ready.  I said I needed a ride. I was told they do not have anyone available at this time. They would call me when they did.  I waited until almost 3:30. I called the dealership back. I was told they just found someone that could get me. Then I waited another 45 minutes for the ride.  When I picked up my Jeep my front passenger door window was down about 4 inches and would not go up or down. Ended up being a repair I would have to do. They would not repair unless I paid to have it repaired.  All the windows were up when I left my vehicle that morning. My thought  is someone slammed the door that broke the cable on the regulator. The next day I tried no less than 6 times to call Robert, the service manager, who was always busy or not in. The operator told me I needed to leave  him a voice mail with my name and number and he would call me back. I left Robert  a voice mail with my name and number on 8/9/16 . I AM STILL WAITING AND IT IS MONDAY THE 15TH. Robert don't waste my time now with a phone call. My Jeep is a 2003 with low miles and very clean, at no time during any of the work being done was my seat covered with plastic to protect the vehicle seat from the dirty clothes of the mechanics.  My Jeep now gets 13.7 miles per gallon, it was getting 18.2 miles per gallon before they worked on it.  I will never buy, recommend or have any work done on any of my vehicles at Lodi CDJR.  I was thinking of buying a new Grand Cherokee Jeep and pass this one to one of my grand kids. If I do it will not be from this dealership.
For the mileage problem I found the cover from the air cleaner to the top of the fuel injection installed wrong. I reinstalled the cover and retrained the computer and now I have my good mileage back.  It is really to bad when the customer has to repair what the professionals work on. My personal recommendation use caution and think twice before dealing with Lodi CDJR.</Text>
